Package <Unnamed>

Class Summary
Die A Die is simply an extended version of a Random object with a specified limit that can be used to simulate rolling a die.
Monopoly This version of Monopoly uses Player, Property, and Die to simulate playing a game of Monopoly using text based input and output (game is played at the command line).
Player A Player can be used to store information about and simulate the actions of a Monopoly player.
Property A Property is used to store information about all of the buyable locations on a Monopoly board.
